                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-09T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 9—3:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Your telegram No. 6, February 6, 6 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d665fn2">See
                        footnote 96, <ref target="#pg_820">p. 820</ref>.</note> Does Captain O’Neill
                    intend to demonstrate before Argentine Army and Navy air service? What
                    information have you as to approximate date of his arrival in Argentina and does
                    he intend to arrive by air or by ship?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
